WEREBEAR

Werebears are among the largest and most physically powerful of the were-
creatures.  Their transformation grants immense Supernatural Strength and
Endurance and an MDC body rivaling gargoyles.  Werebear communities are
reclusive, preferring remote wilderness over civilization.  They are
generally less aggressive than werewolves but vastly more dangerous when
provoked.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 3-18   ME: 3-18   MA: 3-18   PS: 13-38 (Supernatural)
  PP: 3-18   PE: 12-32  PB: 3-18   Spd: 7-22

DAMAGE POOL:
  MDC: 3d6 x10 + 50 (approx 80-230 MDC)
  HP: PE + 2d6

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - MDC body: immune to SDC/HP weapons
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance (highest PS of lycanthropes)
  - Rapid regeneration: 2d6 MDC per melee round
  - Enhanced smell
  - Immunity to non-silver weapons

PENALTIES:
  - Not OCC eligible
  - Vulnerable to silver: double damage
  - Below-average Spd compared to werewolf
  - Lycanthropy risk

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Any (Werebears trend toward Unprincipled or Anarchist).

See also: werewolf, weretiger, races
